%20personal%20finance%20writer%20at%20NerdWallet%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20former%2C%20enrollees%20may%20be%20left%20vulnerable%20without%20coverage%20and%20scrambling%20to%20find%20a%20new%20plan.%20In%20the%20event%20that%20a%20merger%20happens%2C%20enrollees%20could%20end%20up%20auto-enrolled%20into%20a%20plan%20that's%20no%20longer%20a%20good%20fit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20older%20Americans%20depend%20on%20Medicare%20to%20pay%20for%20services%20like%20prescriptions%20and%20doctor%20visits.%20The%20federal%20insurance%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20often%20tied%20to%20Social%20Security%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etypically%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eapplies%20to%20people%20over%2065%20%E2%80%94%20is%20many%20baby%20boomers'%20main%20source%20of%20health%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20health%20insurance%20programs%2C%20recipients%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20a%20yearly%20enrollment%20period.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEligible%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAmericans%20can%20now%20join%2C%20drop%2C%20or%20switch%20their%20supplemental%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMedicare%20plans%20through%20December%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAyoola%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20beneficiaries%20don't%20take%20action%20to%20adjust%20their%20health%20insurance%20plans%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebefore%20December%207%2C%20they%20could%20soon%20see%20higher%20out-of-pocket%20costs%2C%20reduced%20care%20options%2C%20or%20more%20limited%20drug%20coverage%20%E2%80%94%20issues%20that%20can't%20be%20resolved%20after%20the%20enrollment%20period%20closes.%20However%2C%20some%20beneficiaries%20will%20see%20price%20increases%20or%20loss%20of%20coverage%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20people%20who%20are%20budgeting%2C%20open%20enrollment%20is%20especially%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Ayoola%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it's%20a%20time%20to%20do%20comparison%20shopping%20and%20essentially%20see%20if%20you%20can%20find%20a%20cheaper%20plan%20somewhere%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3b5c956-9bb8-42f1-a537-cbb0530bd1eb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedicare%20changes%20on%20the%20horizon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20estimate%20shared%20with%20BI%20from%20Healthpilot%2C%20a%20technology%20platform%20that%20helps%20customers%20choose%20Medicare%20plans%2C%20suggests%20that%20millions%20of%20older%20Americans%20could%20lose%20part%20of%20their%20Medicare%20benefits%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHealthpilot%20estimates%20that%20there%20will%20be%201.5%20million%20people%20impacted%20by%20Medicare%20Advantage%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eplan%20cancellations%20and%202.5%20million%20impacted%20by%20prescription%20drug%20coverage%20cancellations%2C%20due%20in%20part%20to%20insurance%20consolidation.%20Former%20beneficiaries%20of%20those%20plans%20will%20need%20to%20find%20new%20coverage%20to%20replace%20them%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Medicare%20program%20has%20a%20few%20different%20branches%3A%20Parts%20A%20and%20B%20act%20as%20stand-alone%20health%20insurance%20programs%20and%20cover%20all%20types%20of%20inpatient%20and%20outpatient%20care%2C%20while%20Part%20D%20programs%20typically%20cover%20prescription%20drugs%20and%20basic%20provider%20visits%20as%20a%20supplement%20to%20people's%20private%20insurance%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20C%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Medicare%20Advantage%2C%20allows%20seniors%20to%20join%20plans%20that%20are%20offered%20by%20private%20companies%20but%20are%20governed%20by%20Medicare%20rules.%20Advantage%20plans%20have%20their%20own%20caps%20on%20how%20much%20patients%20can%20spend%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20and%20those%20numbers%20change%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20beneficiaries%20with%20Part%20A%20and%20B%20Medicare%20could%20see%20premium%20adjustments%2C%20most%20major%20changes%20will%20occur%20for%20people%20with%20supplemental%20Part%20D%20and%20Medicare%20Advantage%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20increasing%20number%20of%20Medicare%20Advantage%20and%20prescription%20drug%20plans%20are%20setting%20their%20deductible%2C%20or%20the%20amount%20of%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20patients%20are%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20before%20the%20plan%20kicks%20in%2C%20at%20the%20maximum%20allowed%20amount.%20Healthpilot%20found%20that%2010%25%20of%20Medicare%20Advantage%20plans%20will%20be%20at%20the%20maximum%20deductible%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%205%25%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Medicare%20Advantage%20beneficiaries%20will%20still%20have%20prescription%20drug%20coverage%20in%20the%20new%20year%2C%20but%20they%20may%20face%20higher%20out-of-pocket%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20the%20number%20of%20Medicare%20Advantage%20plans%20with%20drug%20benefits%20is%20largely%20holding%20steady%2C%20dropping%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E2%25.%20But%20within%20the%20group%20of%20Medicare%20Advantage%20plans%20that%20still%20have%20drug%20benefits%2C%20the%20number%20of%20%240%20deductible%20plans%20will%20be%20cut%20in%20half%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20more%20plans%20with%20prescription%20drug%20coverage%20will%20have%20higher%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20upfront.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20not%20all%20older%20adults%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewill%20be%20negatively%20affected%20by%20the%20changes.%20Some%20might%20also%20have%20employer-sponsored%20or%20private%20healthcare%20coverage%20outside%20of%20Medicare%2C%20or%20have%20plans%20that%20aren't%20changing.%20But%20for%20the%20Americans%20who%20are%20impacted%2C%20the%20changes%20could%20mean%20healthcare%20becomes%20even%20more%20of%20a%20financial%20strain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d1f7aa47-9bcf-4b2a-8bec-905fe0b5a63c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBaby%20boomers%20are%20already%20struggling%20with%20healthcare%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changing%20Medicare%20costs%20come%20as%20many%20low-income%20baby%20boomers%20are%20struggling%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20medical%20bills.%20Two%20older%20Americans%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20their%20fears%20for%20what%20could%20happen%20if%20their%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20rise%20in%20the%20new%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELisa%20Callejas%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworried%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20her%20husband%20got%20sick%20next%20year.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20they%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20treatment%20%E2%80%94%20her%20husband's%20Medicare%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20will%20go%20up%20to%20%2414%2C000%20from%20around%20%249%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20means%20we%20better%20not%20get%20sick%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECallejas%2C%2055%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20his%20native%20Mexico%20over%20the%20summer%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20save%20money.%20Their%20son%20died%20in%20January%2C%20and%20Callejas'%20husband%2C%20who%20worked%20with%20their%20son%20in%20the%20family%20business%20of%20home%20remodeling%2C%20can%20no%20longer%20do%20the%20manual%20labor%20necessary%20to%20keep%20operations%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20rising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-social-security-baby-boomers-without-savings-401k-poverty-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20it%20increasingly%20difficult%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20US%20on%20a%20lower%20income.%20They're%20living%20off%20the%20money%20they%20made%20from%20selling%20their%20house%20in%20the%20US%20and%20her%20husband's%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-living-social-security-government-aid-snap-loneliness-crisis-isolation-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20benefits%2C%20but%20fearful%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetty%2C%20similarly%2C%20goes%20to%20her%20dialysis%20appointments%20three%20times%20a%20week.%20She%20was%20diagnosed%20wit