how%2F114460002.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prices%20are%20improving.%20So%20why%20is%20everyone%20still%20so%20worked%20up%20about%20inflation%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Angry%20eyebrows%20over%20crumpled-up%20bills%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67126500a0a0cc14f221f64e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%202022%2C%20when%20inflation%20hit%20a%2040-year%20high%20of%209%25%2C%20Americans%20have%20been%20pissed%20off%20about%20the%20economy.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F05%2F23%2Fpublics-positive-economic-ratings-slip-inflation-still-widely-viewed-as-major-problem%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20in%20May%2C%20only%2023%25%20had%20a%20positive%20view%20of%20economic%20conditions.%20And%20when%20asked%20to%20identify%20%26quot%3Bvery%20big%20problems%26quot%3B%20facing%20the%20country%2C%20their%20top%20concern%20wasn't%20immigration%2C%20gun%20violence%2C%20crime%2C%20or%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20inflation.%20Pollsters%20say%20the%20sour%20economic%20mood%20could%20help%20tip%20the%20election%20to%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20as%20voters%20continue%20to%20fret%20over%20the%20price%20of%20milk%20and%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20thing%20is%2C%20wages%20have%20actually%20caught%20up%20with%20inflation.%20Prices%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-september-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoderating%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Unemployment%20is%20low.%20Inequality%20is%20shrinking.%20Financially%2C%20Americans%20are%20better%20off%20than%20they%20were%20before%20prices%20took%20off%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20So%20why%20is%20everyone%20still%20fixated%20on%20inflation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20may%20lie%20in%20a%20new%20paper%20published%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32956%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Traditionally%2C%20economists%20(being%20economists)%20have%20focused%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3Eeconomic%3C%2Fem%3E%20costs%20of%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20i.e.%2C%20are%20price%20increases%20wiping%20out%20everyone's%20annual%20raise%3F%20But%20the%20new%20study%2C%20intriguingly%2C%20examines%20the%20%3Cem%3Eemotional%3C%2Fem%3E%20cost%20of%20inflation.%20How%20do%20high%20prices%20make%20people%20%3Cem%3Efeel%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20regardless%20of%20their%20financial%20circumstances%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%2C%20researchers%20found%2C%20lies%20in%20the%20relationship%20between%20inflation%20and%20wages.%20In%20a%20normal%20economy%2C%20the%20small%20raises%20companies%20give%20are%20enough%20to%20offset%20the%20minimal%20inflation%20we%20typically%20see.%20But%20when%20prices%20spike%2C%20companies%20still%20default%20to%20giving%20more%20or%20less%20the%20same%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-increase-2023-projections-raise-inflation-jobs-wages-income-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20raises%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20presents%20workers%20with%20a%20dilemma.%20Do%20they%20accept%20the%20tiny%20increase%20and%20watch%20their%20standard%20of%20living%20fall%3F%20Or%20do%20they%20ask%20their%20boss%20for%20a%20bigger%20raise%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20of%203%2C000%20workers%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20most%20%E2%80%94%20a%20whopping%2079%25%20%E2%80%94%20just%20accepted%20the%20salary%20they%20were%20offered.%20Only%2021%25%20took%20action%20to%20secure%20a%20bigger%20raise.%20And%20doing%20that%20put%20them%20in%20a%20situation%20people%20really%20hate%3A%20They%20had%20to%20enter%20into%20conflict%20with%20their%20employer.%20Trying%20to%20land%20a%20bigger%20raise%20meant%20doing%20things%20like%20having%20a%20difficult%20conversation%20with%20their%20boss%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-raise-controversial-tactic-job-interview-counteroffer-employer-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecuring%20a%20job%20offer%20from%20a%20different%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20use%20as%20negotiating%20leverage%2C%20switching%20jobs%20entirely%2C%20or%20having%20their%20union%20negotiate%20on%20their%20behalf.%20Inflation%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20requires%20people%20to%20fight%20for%20better%20pay%2C%20which%20takes%20a%20toll%20on%20their%20emotional%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20find%20that%20conflict%20with%20employers%20is%20costly%20to%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20write.%20%26quot%3BInflation%20imposes%20costs%20on%20workers%20beyond%20its%20impact%20on%20real%20wages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20workers%20are%20so%20averse%20to%20conflict%2C%20most%20avoided%20negotiating%20for%20a%20raise%20even%20though%20they%20believed%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20have%20paid%20off%20financially.%20Those%20who%20didn't%20put%20up%20a%20fight%20knew%20they%20were%20paying%20a%20price%3A%20Had%20they%20gone%20to%20bat%20for%20themselves%2C%20they%20predicted%2C%20they%20would%20have%20boosted%20their%20salary%20by%202%20percentage%20points.%20The%20fact%20that%20they%20didn't%20suggests%20something%20powerful%3A%20Most%20people%20hate%20conflict%20so%20much%20that%20they'd%20rather%20leave%20money%20on%20the%20table%20rather%20than%20speak%20up%20for%20themselves.%20The%20median%20worker%2C%20the%20researchers%20calculated%2C%20was%20willing%20to%20give%20up%201.75%25%20of%20their%20salary%20to%20avoid%20the%20anxiety%20and%20hassle%20of%20negotiating.%20Most%20of%20us%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20would%20rather%20let%20inflation%20screw%20us%20over%20than%20put%20the%20screws%20to%20our%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThinking%20about%20inflation%20this%20way%20%E2%80%94%20as%20having%20both%20an%20economic%20and%20an%20emotional%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20me%20make%20better%20sense%20of%20all%20the%20strife%20that's%20been%20roiling%20the%20American%20workplace%20in%20recent%20years.%20Some%20of%20it%2C%20as%20I've%20reported%2C%20was%20spurred%20by%20the%20red-hot%20job%20market%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-great-reshuffle-upward-mobility-quitting-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreat%20Resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20shifted%20the%20balance%20of%20power%20between%20workers%20and%20their%20employers.%20Some%20of%20it%20arose%20from%20the%20ongoing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-defying-orders-return-to-office-great-resistance-remote-work-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewar%20over%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20some%20of%20it%20has%20been%20driven%20by%20historic%20shifts%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20white-collar%20professionals%20began%20facing%20the%20same%20threat%20of%20mass%20layoffs%20that%20blue-collar%20workers%20have%20long%20experienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20poring%20over%20the%20new%20study%2C%20I%20realize%20I%20overlooked%20the%20role%20inflation%20has%20played%20in%20reshaping%20the%20pandemic-era%20workplace.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20I've%20repeatedly%20heard%20a%20sense%20of%20injustice%20from%20the%20workers%20I've%20spoken%20with%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feeling%20that%20there's%20something%20fundamentally%20unfair%20about%20having%20to%20accept%20what%20is%20essentially%20an%20inflation-adjusted%20pay%20cut.%20HR%20departments%20don't%20benchmark%20salaries%20against%20inflation%2C%20but%20employees%20think%20they%20should.%20And%20the%20faster%20prices%20rise%2C%20the%20study%20found%2C%20the%20more%20contentious%20the%20workplace%20becomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReading%20the%20research%2C%20I%20recalled%20a%20conversation%20I'd%20had%20with%20a%20friend%20who%20had%20fought%20for%20a%20raise.%20To%20force%20her%20boss%20to%20pay%20her%20more%2C%20she%20secured%20a%20competing%20offer%20from%20another%20company.%20She%20wound%20up%20getting%20what%20she%20wanted%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20still%20felt%20resentful.%20Why%20couldn't%20her%20employer%20just%20pay%20her%20a%20fair%20salary%20to%20begin%20with%3F%20She%20hated%20having%20to%20go%20through%20all%20that%20drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20how%20hard%20and%20frustrating%20it%20can%20be%20to%20ask%20for%20a%20raise.%20I%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20career%20unwilling%20to%20stomach%20the%20conflict%20involved%20in%20negotiating%20a%20higher%20salary.%20The%20first%20time%20I%20ever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-pay-transparency-jobs-income-taboo-equity-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20for%20more%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20was%20during%20this%20recent%20stretch%20of%20super-high%20inflation.%20And%20even%20then%2C%20I%20agonized%20over%20the%20decision.%20I%20didn't%20want%20my%20boss%20to%20think%20I%20was%20greedy%20or%20ungrateful%2C%20and%20I%20worried%20I%20would%20feel%20rejected%20if%20he%20turned%20me%20down.%20I%20drafted%20and%20redrafted%20my%20request%20more%20times%20than%20I'd%20care%20to%20admit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20literally%20write%20about%20this%20stuff%20for%20a%20living.%20Turns%20out%20I'm%20just%20like%20everyone%20in%20the%20study%3A%20Even%20when%20I%20wound%20up%20getting%20a%20raise%2C%20I%20left%20the%20experience%20wishing%20that%20inflation%20hadn't%20forced%20the%20confrontation%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Rising%20prices%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20me%2C%20beyond%20their%20financial%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%2C%20in%20a%20nutshell%2C%20is%20why%20inflation%20makes%20us%20so%20mad%3A%20It%20dredges%20up%20all%20the%20complicated%20feelings%20we%20have%20about%20our%20relationship%20to%20our%20employers.%20Will%20asking%20for%20a%20raise%20make%20us%20seem%20disloyal%3F%20Will%20%3Cem%3Enot%20%3C%2Fem%3Easking%20for%20a%20raise%20make%20us%20feel%20like%20chumps%3F%20And%20why%20do%20we%20have%20to%20fight%20so%20hard%20to%20make%20sure%20our%20paychecks%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%3F%20In%20a%20normal%20economy%2C%20when%20inflation%20is%20low%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20think%20about%20that%20stuff.%20But%20when%20high%20prices%20start%20eating%20into%20our%20paychecks%2C%20we're%20forced%20to%20reconsider%20the%20value%20of%20our%20labor%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20hard%20we're%20willing%20to%20fight%20for%20it.%20Our%20response%20to%20inflation%20isn't%20about%20the%20price%20of%20eggs.%20It's%20about%20the%20cost%20of%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-hidden-cost-work-salary-negotiation-boss-conflict-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729590302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6712651efd8ede6c99e3b2ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-hidden-cost-work-salary-negotiation-boss-conflict-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20study%20finds%20that%20inflation's%20deepest%20impact%20isn't%20financial%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20emotional.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C