lying-from-nyc-to-michigan-every-week-for-work-supercommuter-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20planned%20to%20spend%20the%20summer%20on%20campus%20working%20on%20an%20independent%20computer%20science%20research%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20before%20the%20summer%20semester%20started%2C%20I%20was%20talking%20to%20a%20friend%20on%20campus%20when%20a%20random%20student%20sat%20down%20to%20join%20our%20chat.%20We%20talked%20about%20nonlinear%20dynamics%20and%20exchanged%20phone%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22714b6817-e5b3-4c40-b120-5508c0bc21e3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20recruited%20me%20to%20live%20in%20a%20hacker%20house%20and%20work%20on%20a%20neurotech%20project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20day%2C%20he%20sent%20me%20a%20message%20explaining%20that%20he%20was%20starting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-how-agi-house-bays-hottest-artificial-intelligence-hacker-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehacker%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmyelingroup.github.io%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMyelin%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20live%20there%20and%20work%20on%20a%20neurotech%20project%20for%20three%20months.%20I%20had%20heard%20of%20hacker%20houses%20before%20but%20didn't%20know%20of%20any%20around%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guy%20I%20met%20and%20three%20other%20students%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Ftech%2Fai%2Fnews%2Fa-living-computer-this-ai-made-from-interconnected-mini-brains-requires-a-million-times-less-power-than-chatgpt%2Farticleshow%2F110909568.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewetware%20computer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20pitched%20the%20idea%20to%20different%20VCs%20and%20other%20organizations%20and%20received%20around%20%248%2C000%20in%20funding%20through%20Emergent%20Ventures%20and%20the%201517%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20had%20the%20funds%2C%20they%20rented%20a%20house%20in%20Ann%20Arbor%20for%20three%20months.%20They%20aimed%20to%20recruit%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20to%20work%20on%20the%20project%2C%20hoping%20it%20would%20become%20a%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20recruited%20me%20because%20he%20thought%20I%20was%20good%20at%20physics.%20The%20project's%20novelty%20seemed%20exciting%2C%20and%20I%20needed%20a%20break%20from%20just%20doing%20coursework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20majoring%20in%20math%2C%20physics%2C%20and%20cognitive%20science.%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20interesting%20now%20instead%20of%20in%20seven%20years.%20After%20learning%20more%20about%20the%20opportunity%2C%20I%20said%20yes.%20I%20moved%20in%20in%20May%202023%2C%20when%20I%20was%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227790a0c3-6eac-4d67-b5ca-f684dea03893%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20got%20free%20rent%20in%20exchange%20for%20helping%20the%20team%20work%20on%20a%20project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20living%20room%20with%20carpet%2C%20chairs%2C%20and%20a%20piano%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6716a8ea9b3250dbbce8e716%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMyelin%20house.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jonah%20Weinbaum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20looked%20for%20summer%20housing%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20I'd%20have%20to%20spend%20around%20%241%2C500%20for%20three%20months.%20It%20was%20a%20big%20draw%20that%20living%20in%20the%20hacker%20house%20came%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-rent-free-nyc-van-student-intern-adventure-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20supplied%20some%20meals%20and%20covered%20the%20utilities.%20All%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20was%20the%20extra%20food%20I%20wanted%2C%20but%20I%20ate%20very%20inexpensively%2C%20so%20my%20bills%20were%20around%20%2430%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20any%20given%20time%2C%207-14%20people%20from%20places%20like%20Michigan%2C%20Washington%2C%20Canada%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20California%20lived%20there.%20Some%20people%20had%20internships%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%20summer%20and%20left%20the%20house%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20was%20a%20student%3B%20some%20were%20later%20in%20their%20careers%2C%20but%20most%20of%20us%20were%20college-aged.%20They%20came%20because%20they%20wanted%20to%20work%20on%20and%20talk%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-neurotech-allows-stroke-survivor-speak-brainwaves-thinking-paralyzed-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneurotech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20such%20places%20aren't%20easy%20to%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20of%20us%20moved%20in%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20picked%20our%20rooms%20(I%20got%20lucky%20and%20had%20my%20own%20room)%2C%20cleaned%20the%20house%2C%20and%20had%20our%20first%20meeting%20about%20the%20project%20and%20how%20we%20would%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22222a08af-7203-4c34-99d8-1ca341d37d3b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvery%20hacker%20house%20operates%20differently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20three%20teams%2C%20each%20with%20three%20or%20four%20people.%20The%20teams%20started%20with%20somebody%20presenting%20an%20idea%20for%20a%20team%2C%20and%20people%20joined%20if%20they%20liked%20it.%20The%20house%20was%20full%20of%20neurotech%20equipment%20and%20people%20working%20on%20projects%20ranging%20from%20personalized%20medicine%20to%20EEG-based%20object%20control%20and%20biological%20neuron%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20we%20woke%20up%2C%20at%20around%209%20a.m.%2C%20we%20started%20working%20on%20the%20project%20and%20worked%20on%20it%20all%20day%20until%20we%20went%20to%20bed%20at%20random%20late%20hours.%20We%20didn't%20do%20anything%20else.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20person%20enrolled%20in%20a%20summer%20class%20and%20completed%20my%20work%20during%20lunch%20or%20dinner%20breaks.%20I%20didn't%20travel%20or%20see%20friends%20outside%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20high-tech%20focus%2C%20life%20in%20the%20house%20was%20simple.%20We%20had%20a%20piano%20that%20was%20played%20at%20regular%20intervals%2C%20food%20in%20the%20fridge%2C%20and%20beds.%20Some%20house%20members%20slept%20less%20than%20others%2C%20so%20there%20was%20almost%20always%20some%20conversation%20in%20the%20living%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2203055209-bf20-48b1-bb79-9d4b4a1c1b2e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20spent%20my%20time%20doing%20research%20and%20sharing%20it%20with%20the%20other%20members%20of%20the%20house%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20goal%20was%20to%20design%20a%20low-cost%20wetware%20computer%20that%20one%20could%20use%20for%20edge%20computer%20applications%20(robotics%2C%20drones%2C%20etc.).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20with%20two%20other%20house%20members%20to%20develop%20a%20new%20paradigm%20for%20wetware%20computing.%20We%20eventually%20found%20a%20set%20of%20plausible%20methodologies%20for%20the%20project%20and%20wrote%20a%20white%20paper%20on%20how%20we%20could%20see%20them%20coming%20together.%20Being%20near%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20campus%20gave%20us%20constant%20opportunities%20to%20speak%20with%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20spend%20our%20days%20talking%20to%20researchers%2C%20reading%20papers%20online%2C%20and%20synthesizing%20everything.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20every%20week%2C%20we'd%20present%20our%20progress%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229f789bd1-74c3-40fe-979a-a181d5696bc2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20your%20time%20at%20a%20hacker%20house%20ends%2C%20the%20community%20doesn't%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20start%20of%20the%20school%20year%2C%20we%20viewed%20our%20operations%20through%20a%20business%20l