turns%20of%20the%20equal-weighted%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20relative%20to%20the%20aggregate%20one%2C%20with%20returns%20fairing%20better%20in%20the%20former%20on%20a%20long-term%20outlook%20and%20in%20sharper%20bouts%20following%20peaks%20of%20elevated%20concentration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221486%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chart%20showing%20equal-weighted%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20versus%20aggregate%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20performance.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6716c856a0a0cc14f222dbd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22882%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20an%20exchange-traded%20fund%20that%20tracks%20the%20equal-weighted%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20could%20be%20one%20way%20to%20go%20about%20it.%20This%20also%20means%20investors%20will%20increase%20their%20exposure%20to%20small-cap%20stocks%2C%20another%20perk%20in%20a%20reversion-to-the-mean%20type%20scenario%2C%20where%20this%20sector%20has%20room%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20investors%20should%20consider%20a%20more%20mixed%20asset%20portfolio%20of%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20without%20tilting%20toward%20one%20more%20than%20the%20other.%20This%20would%20create%20better%20risk-adjusted%20returns.%20Factoring%20in%20the%20types%20of%20yields%20across%20bonds%20is%20another%20option.%20Consider%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20at%20a%20yield%20of%204%25%2C%20investment-grade%20bonds%20at%204.8%25%2C%20and%20high-yield%20bonds%20at%20a%207%25%20yield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20be%20open%20to%20readjusting%20the%20allocation%20tilt%20based%20on%20macroeconomic%20shifts.%20This%20flexibility%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrategic%20tilt%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20May%2028%20note%20led%20by%20the%20head%20of%20asset%20allocation%20research%2C%20Christian%20Mueller-Glissmann.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20economic%20growth%20is%20strong%20but%20there's%20a%20risk%20of%20inflation%2C%20leaning%20more%20into%20equities%2C%20especially%20stocks%20with%20strong%20cash%20flows%2C%20may%20be%20the%20right%20direction.%20Meanwhile%2C%20if%20growth%20is%20slowed%20and%20inflation%20is%20muted%2C%20consider%20further%20allocation%20to%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-beat-stock-market-returns-next-decade-goldman-sachs-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729587602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6716c8f301ea6d83dee305d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-beat-stock-market-returns-next-decade-goldman-sachs-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best-performing%20portfolio%20may%20be%20based%20on%20a%20strategic%20tilt%20that%20factors%20in%20macroeconomic%20shifts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-beat-stock-market-returns-next-decade-goldman-sachs-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'The%20million-dollar%20question%20of%20this%20election'%3A%20Women's%20health%20startups%20are%20confronting%20a%20shifting%20legal%20landscape%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20featuring%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20a%20close-up%20of%20%24100%20bills%2C%20a%20woman%20at%20a%20clinic%2C%20and%20the%20female%20gender%20symbol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67129d1c01ea6d83dee27b03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Bell%3B%20Kevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20full%20day%20of%20meetings%20at%20Julie%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20sells%20a%20morning-after%20pill%2C%20CEO%20Amanda%20E%2FJ%20Morrison%20jumped%20a%20flight%20from%20New%20York%20to%20Boston%20and%20headed%20to%20a%20small%2C%20private%20college%2C%20where%20a%20trivia%20night%20awaited%20her.%20Dozens%20of%20students%20shuffled%20into%20a%20classroom%20with%20plates%20of%20chicken%20tenders%2C%20Texas%20toast%2C%20and%20bright%20blue%20boxes%20of%20the%20emergency%20contraceptive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorrison%20had%20worked%20with%20the%20Planned%20Parenthood%20Generation%20Action%20club%20at%20Suffolk%20University%20to%20sponsor%20the%20event%2C%20part%20of%20Julie's%20efforts%20to%20win%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20consumers.%20However%2C%20she%20had%20another%2C%20more%20pressing%20reason%20for%20being%20there.%20Julie%20is%20doing%20more%20campus%20events%20to%20clear%20up%20some%20of%20the%20confusion%20about%20emergency%20contraception%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20that%20it%20isn't%20medication%20abortion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStanding%20at%20the%20head%20of%20the%20classroom%2C%20Morrison%20read%20off%20a%20projector%20screen%2C%20%26quot%3BEmergency%20contraceptives%20like%20Julie%20are%20legal%20in%20how%20many%20states%3F%2025%2C%2048%2C%2050%2C%2037.%26quot%3B%20Students%20tapped%20their%20answers%20into%20a%20quiz%20app.%20%26quot%3BIt's%2037%2C%26quot%3B%20Lily%2C%20a%20spirited%20sophomore%2C%20whispered%20to%20her%20teammates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20minute%2C%20the%20correct%20answer%20appeared%20on%20screen%2C%20and%20the%20quiet%20chatter%20rose%20to%20a%20clamor.%20Half%20the%20teams%20said%2037%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFifty%20states%2C%20guys.%20It's%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Morrison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20why%20she%20said%2037%2C%20Lily%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJust%20the%20way%20things%20are%20going.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20states%20that%20outlaw%20abortion%2C%20some%20patients%20and%20politicians%20worry%20that%20contraception%20could%20be%20in%20legal%20jeopardy%2C%20too.%20There's%20no%20federal%20law%20preserving%20access%20to%20birth%20control%2C%20rather%2C%20a%20patchwork%20of%20state%20laws%20and%20court%20decisions%20holding%20it%20in%20place.%20Another%20Trump%20term%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F05%2F29%2Ftrump-birth-control-contraception-00159555%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20change%20that%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Julie%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20the%20million%20dollar%20question%20of%20this%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20Morrison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TK%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67127928fd8ede6c99e3c27f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStudents%20with%20the%20Suffolk%20University%20chapter%20of%20Planned%20Parenthood%20Generation%20Action%20hold%20up%20prizes%20at%20a%20trivia%20night%20hosted%20by%20Julie%2C%20an%20emergency-contraception%20startup.%3Cp%3EJulie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20worried%20about%20some%20big%20ban%20happening%20in%20the%20first%20hundred%20days.%20But%20how%20those%20decisions%20trickle%20down%20%E2%80%94%20what%20is%20presented%20in%20Congress%20as%20a%20bill%2C%20how%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20reacts%2C%20what%20trickles%20down%20to%20the%20states%20%E2%80%94%20becomes%20a%20real%20secondary%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounders%20of%20women's%20health%20startups%20feel%20doubly%20invested%20in%20this%20election%2C%20one%20of%20the%20closest%20presidential%20races%20of%20the%20century.%20Half%20a%20dozen%20founders%20and%20investors%20of%20women's%20health%20companies%2C%20all%20women%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20if%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20wins%2C%20it's%20business%20as%20usual.%20They%20said%20another%20Trump%20victory%20creates%20uncertainty%20for%20reproductive%20health%20startups%2C%20from%20period%20trackers%20to%20online%20abortion%20clinics%20to%20embryo%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222147%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TK%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6712959a01ea6d83dee25963%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221610%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20startup%20Julie%2C%20the%20legal%20status%20of%20emergency%20contraception%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmillion%20dollar%20question%20of%20this%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amanda%20E%2FJ%20Morrison.%3Cp%3EJulie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Harris's%20presidential%20campaign%20has%20been%20marked%20by%20unrelenting%20support%20for%20reproductive%20healthcare%2C%20including%20contraception%20and%20abortions%2C%20Trump's%20position%20has%20been%20a%20moving%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F05%2F29%2Ftrump-birth-control-contraception-00159555%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Blooking%20at%26quot%3B%20restrictions%20on%20birth%20control%2C%20then%20walked%20that%20position%20back%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post%20later%20that%20day.%20During%20the%20September%20presidential%20debate%2C%20he%20called%20himself%20a%20%26quot%3Bleader%26quot%3B%20on%20IVF%2C%20a%20move%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F09%2F12%2Ftrump-ivf-gop-roe-abortion-00178760%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eangered%3C%2Fa%3E%20parts%20of%20his%20base%20that%20have%20sought%20to%20restrict%20fertility%20treatments.%20He%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fdonald-trump-says-he-would-veto-federal-abortion-ban%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20October%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he'd%20veto%20a%20national%20abortion%20ban%20after%20deflecting%20the%20question%20for%20months%20but%20would%20support%20states%20ordaining%20their%20own%20abortion%20bans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20waffling%20on%20reproductive%20rights%20has%20put%20founders%20of%20women's%20health%20startups%20on%20notice.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20issues%20that%20we're%20discussing%20and%20that%20our%20CEOs%20are%20focused%20on%20%E2%80%94%20how%20to%20continue%20to%20provide%20care%20to%20women%2C%20especially%20women%20of%20childbearing%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Trish%20Costello%2C%20founder%20of%20Portfolia%2C%20an%20investing%20platform%20that%20pools%20money%20from%20female%20accredited%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20after%20the%20presidential%20debate%2C%20Mika%20Eddy%20was%20vibrating%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20election.%20The%20race's%20outcome%20could%20drastically%20change%20reproductive%20rights%2C%20foreign%20policy%2C%20gun%20safety%2C%20and%20climate%20law%20%E2%80%94%20all%20issues%20close%20to%20Eddy%2C%20a%2035-year-old%20Californian%20and%20mother%20of%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Eddy%20also%20has%20skin%20in%20the%20game%20as%20the%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Malama%20Health%2C%20a%20startup%20helping%20women%20with%20gestational%20diabetes%20access%20better%20care.%20Its%20doula%20network%20assists%20patients%20on%20Medicaid%20with%20applying%20for%20benefits%20such%20as%20diabetes-friendly%20meals%20and%20medical%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddy%20worries%20that%20if%20Trump%20wins%2C%20he%20would%20restrict%20access%20to%20the%20coverage%20and%20benefits%20that%20her%20users%20rely%20on%2C%20weakening%20one%20of%20Malama%20Health's%20key%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20this%20common%20misperception%20that%2C%20'we're%20in%20California%2C%20we're%20in%20a%20liberal%20state%2C%20and%20so%20we're%20safe.'%20And%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Eddy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20founders%20of%20women's%20health%20startups%2C%20this%20election%20is%20more%20than%20a%20political%20contest%3B%20it%20has%20ramifications%20for%20their%20livelihoods.%20With%20so%20much%20at%20stake%2C%20they're%20planning%20how%20to%20handle%20a%20scenario%20where%20states%20or%20courts%20might%20impose%20more%20limits%20on%20reproductive%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20taking%20pictures%20with%20some%20young%20teen%20girls.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671287fafd8ede6c99e3cf6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKamala%20Harris%20wants%20Congress%20to%20pass%20a%20national%20law%20codifying%20access%20to%20abortion.%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Corum%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabortion-telemedicine-startup-hey-jane-roe-v-wade-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHey%20Jane%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20telehealth%20startup%20that%20connects%20patients%20to%20medical%20providers%20who%20offer%20online%20appointments%20and%20delivers%20abortion%20pills%20to%20their%20doorsteps.%20A%20year%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20overruled%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%2C%20ending%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20abortion%2C%20Hey%20Jane%20started%20selling%20birth%20control%20and%20treatments%20for%20urinary%20tract%20infections%2C%20yeast%20infections%2C%20and%20herpes%2C%20both%20oral%20and%20genital.%20The%20new%20products%20cushion%20the%20business%20against%20a%20%26quot%3Bplan%20E%26quot%3B%20scenario%20of%20a%20national%20abortion%20ban%2C%20said%20Carli%20Sapir%2C%20a%20Hey%20Jane%20investor%20and%20founding%20partner%20of%20Amboy%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20thinking%20about%20how%20to%20make%20sure%20those%20other%20verticals%20are%20in%20a%20good%20place%20to%20continue%20carrying%20the%20company%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sapir.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20last%20year%2C%20one%20of%20Hey%20Jane's%20rivals%2C%20Choix%2C%20shut%20down%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvcs-backing-online-abortion-sites-say-its-good-business-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafter%20three%20years%20in%20service%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fchoix-closes-virtual-doors-launches-130300919.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20stigma%20and%20politics%20surrounding%20abortion%20care%20posed%20significant%20fundraising%20challenges.%26quot%3B%20It%20raised%20a%20%241%20million%20seed%20round%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20direct%20providers%20of%20abortion%2C%20like%20Hey%20Jane%2C%20could%20see%20major%20restrictions%20or%20shutdowns%20to%20their%20core%20businesses%20if%20Trump%20returns%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20companies%20expect%20to%20feel%20the%20ripple%20effects.%20Startups%20that%20seem%20removed%20from%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20such%20as%20those%20involved%20with%20period%20tracking%20and%20fertility%20treatments%2C%20are%20also%20preparing%20for%20potential%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Then-President%20Donald%20Trump%20addresses%20the%20anti-abortion%20%26quot%3BMarch%20for%20Life%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6712790ffd8ede6c99e3c272%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%202020%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20became%20the%20first%20sitting%20president%20to%20attend%20the%20anti-abortion%20%26quot%3BMarch%20for%20Life%26quot%3B%20rally.%3Cp%3EMark%20Wilson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20national%20abortion%20ban%20were%20to%20occur%2C%20apps%20like%20Flo%20Health%20or%20Clue%20might%20face%20increased%20scrutiny%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-lux-capital-deena-shakir-wrote-childrens-book-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeena%20Shakir%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20Lux%20Capital.%20These%20apps%20track%20when%20women%20have%20their%20periods%20and%20when%20they%20miss%20them.%20In%20today's%20post-Roe%20America%2C%20privacy%20experts%20worry%20that%20such%20data%20could%20be%20used%20to%20suggest%20that%20someone%20has%20had%20or%20is%20thinking%20about%20having%20an%20abortion%2C%20potentially%20putting%20women%20at%20risk%20of%20prosecution%20in%20certain%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20could%20be%20equally%20high%20for%20companies%20involved%20with%20fertility%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20services%20like%20in%20vitro%20fertilization%2C%20or%20IVF%2C%20and%20surrogacy%20has%20been%20climbing%20for%20years%20as%20people%20have%20kids%20later%20in%20life%20and%20infertility%20rates%20increase.%20That's%20birthed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffertility-startups-booming-despite-market-downturn-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20fertility%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20includes%20companies%20that%20operate%20clinics%20to%20provide%20services%20like%20egg%20freezing%20and%20IVF%2C%20companies%20that%20run%20labs%20and%20tests%2C%20and%20firms%20that%20help%20people%20pay%20for%20the%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20industry's%20future%20is%20uncertain%20following%20attacks%20on%20abortion%20access.%20The%20end%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20opened%20up%20the%20legal%20terrain%20for%20states%20to%20interfere%20with%20access%20to%20other%20reproductive%20care%2C%20said%20Lauren%20Berson%20Sugarman%2C%20founder%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Conceive%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20offers%20personalized%20fertility%20guidance%2C%20including%20text%20support%20from%20nurses%20and%20peer%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Alabama%2C%20the%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20frozen%20embryos%20should%20be%20considered%20children.%20That%20put%20patients%20and%20fertility%20clinics%20on%20edge%20that%20they%20could%20be%20criminally%20charged%20for%20destroying%20extra%20embryos.%20A%20handful%20of%20Alabama%20clinics%20paused%20IVF%20treatments%20while%20patients%20throughout%20the%20South%20began%20moving%20their%20embryos%20to%20jurisdictions%20with%20more%20stable%20legal%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20patients%20come%20to%20us%20and%20say%2C%20should%20I%20move%20my%20embryos%20out%20of%20a%20red%20state%3F%20Because%20what%20happens%20if%20they%20come%20after%20IVF%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Berson%20Sugarman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20%26quot%3Bembryo%20rights%26quot%3B%20could%20have%20wide-reaching%20repercussions%20for%20startups%20like%20Maven%20Clinic%20or%20Carrot%20Fertility%2C%20which%20offer%20fertility%20benefits%20for%20employers%2C%20and%20TMRW%20Life%20Sciences%2C%20a%20biotech%20company%20creating%20robots%20for%20the%20safe%20storage%20of%20frozen%20sperm%2C%20eggs%2C%20and%20embryos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20it%20could%20influence%20the%20type%20of%20research%20that%20startups%20conduct%20and%20where.%20Alice%20Zheng%2C%20a%20principal%20at%20women's%20health%20investor%20RH%20Capital%2C%20explains%20how%20the%20shifting%20legal%20landscape%20might%20affect%20companies%20like%20Vitra%20Labs.%20As%20a%20biotech%20startup%20working%20on%20developing%20eggs%20from%20stem%20cells%20for%20IVF%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20doing%20really%20cutting-edge%20research%20for%20fertility%2C%20but%20they%20need%20to%20think%20very%20carefully%20about%20where%20they%20set%20up%20shop%2C%26quot%3B%20Zheng%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20their%20research%20might%20involve%20certain%20types%20of%20tissue%2C%20which%20is%20more%20closely%20scrutinized%20in%20some%20areas%20than%20others.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TK%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671296ec01ea6d83dee25ec8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20emergency%20contraception%20is%20not%20the%20abortion%20bill%20and%20is%20currently%20legal%20in%20all%2050%20states%2C%20it%20is%20continuously%20confused%20with%20the%20abortion%20pill%2C%20which%20can%20have%20damaging%20consequences.%3Cp%3EJulie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20in%20the%20hours%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ended%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20an%20abortion%2C%20Morrison's%20phone%20started%20ringing%20and%20didn't%20stop.%20Investors%20wanted%20to%20know%20if%20the%20ruling%20would%20kill%20Julie's%20launch%20in%20Walmart%20stores%20that%20fall.%20Job%20candidates%20wondered%20if%20the%20company%20would%20still%20exist%20in%20six%20months.%20Morrison's%20mom%20called%2C%20concerned%20for%20her%20daughter's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20probably%20two%20weeks%20straight%2C%20I%20was%20just%20doing%20reassurance%20calls%2C%26quot%3B%20Morrison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20emergency%20contraception%20is%20not%20the%20abortion%20bill%20and%20is%20currently%20legal%20in%20all%2050%20states%2C%20it%20is%20continuously%20confused%20with%20the%20abortion%20pill%2C%20which%20can%20have%20damaging%20consequences.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20medical%20journal%20JAMA%20Network%20Open%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2820370%3F%2520utm_source%3DFor_The_Media%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%20retail%20pharmacy%20fills%20of%20Plan%20B%2C%20a%20leading%20morning-after%20pill%20brand%2C%20fell%20by%2065%25%20in%20states%20with%20near-total%20abortion%20bans%20the%20year%20after%20the%20Dobbs%20decision%2C%20partly%20due%20to%20clinic%20closures%20and%20confusion%20about%20its%20legal%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20confusion%20could%20threaten%20Julie's%20sales%2C%20and%20puts%20the%20onus%20of%20the%20company%20to%20better%20educate%20consumers.%20It%20sponsors%20events%20like%20trivia%20nights%20and%20sorority%20house%20brunches.%20It%20has%20enlisted%20TikTok%20influencers%20to%20share%20videos%20of%20their%20drugstore%20hauls%20showing%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20buy%20Julie.%20In%20one%20video%2C%20a%20young%20woman%20going%20back-to-school%20shopping%20walks%20off%20with%20a%20two-count%20pack%20of%20the%20emergency%20contraceptive%20pill.%20The%20caption%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20majors%2C%20not%20double%20strollers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20startups%20are%20urging%20consumers%20to%20fight%20for%20reproductive%20rights%20at%20the%20polls.%20Eddy's%20Malama%20Health%20has%20reminders%20to%20register%20to%20vote%20in%20its%20app%20and%20will%20tell%20users%20where%20their%20nearest%20polling%20station%20is%20closer%20to%20election%20day.%20The%20company%20asks%20for%20their%20ZIP%20codes%20during%20onboarding%2C%20Eddy%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20you're%20like%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20vote%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20where%20to%20go%2C'%26quot%3B%20Eddy%20said.%20She%20hopes%20the%20emails%20will%20get%20more%20pregnant%20women%20and%20new%20moms%20to%20head%20to%20the%20polls.%20Eddy%20added%20that%20the%20emails%20won't%20support%20a%20candidate%20and%20are%20meant%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnonpartisan%20resource.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TK%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67127bd2a0a0cc14f2220d4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20student%20at%20trivia%20night%20asked%20Amanda%20E%2FJ%20Morrison%20(right)%20to%20sign%20her%20Julie-branded%20T-shirt.%3Cp%3EJulie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJulie's%20content%20isn't%20political%2C%20either.%20It's%20not%20trying%20to%20change%20any%20minds%20about%20abortion%20rights.%20The%20goal%20is%20simply%20to%20spread%20awareness%20among%20young%20adults%20that%20emergency%20contraception%20helps%20prevent%20pregnancy%2C%20not%20end%20it.%20This%20way%2C%20Morrison%20said%2C%20a%20woman%20who%20is%20anti-abortion%20and%20has%20unprotected%20sex%20can%20feel%20confident%20taking%20Julie%20knowing%20that%20she%20isn't%20compromising%20her%20abortion%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20past%209%20o'clock%20on%20a%20weekday%2C%20and%20the%20competition%20at%20trivia%20night%20was%20heating%20up.%20Students%20in%20teams%20of%20two%20or%20three%20screamed%20with%20delight%20as%20they%20watched%20their%20names%20climb%20the%20leaderboard.%20They%20competed%20to%20win%20prizes%20like%20sex%20toys%20and%20T-shirts%20with%20the%20phrase%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20Better%20Morning%20After.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMorning-after%20pills%20end%20pregnancy.%20True%20or%20false%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20club%20president%20called%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirty%20seconds%20later%2C%20the%20screen%20showed%20that%20every%20team%20had%20answered%20correctly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorrison%20pumped%20both%20fists%20in%20the%20air%2C%20beaming%20her%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmelia-russell%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EMelia%20Russell%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider%20covering%20startups%20and%20venture%20capital.%20She%20can%20be%20reached%20via%20the%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20%2B1%20603-913-3085%20and%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amrussell%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emrussell%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Frebecca-torrenc