amples%20from%20Chhattisgarh's%20Durg%2C%20Rajnandgaon%2C%20Kanker%2C%20Bemetara%2C%20Balod%2C%20and%20Kawardha%20found%20uranium%20levels%20in%20excess%20of%20100%20micrograms%20per%20litre%3B%20one%20sample%20from%20a%20village%20in%20Balod%20had%20as%20much%20130%20micrograms%20per%20litre%20and%20another%20from%20Kanker%20had%20106%20micrograms%20per%20litre.%20Across%20the%20six%20districts%20the%20average%20reading%20was%2086%20to%20105%20micrograms%20of%20uranium%20per%20litre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20samples%20tested%20were%20from%20a%2025-year-old%20borewell%20in%20Balod's%20Devtarai%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20were%20double-checked%20by%20the%20state's%20Public%20Health%20Emergency%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20other%20source%20of%20water%20in%20the%20village...%20one%20day%20we%20came%20to%20know%20that%20research%20was%20done%20and%20some%20students%20took%20water%20from%20here%2C%20in%20which%20uranium%20was%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20Daneshwar%20Sinha%2C%20the%20village%20chief%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3B...%20after%20that%20we%20ran%20to%20the%20PHE%20Department%20and%20it%20was%20tested%20once%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20village%20has%20now%20opened%20a%20second%20bore%2C%20but%20it%20is%20unclear%20if%20the%20source%20of%20that%20water%20is%20different%20from%20the%20first%20or%20if%20uranium%20levels%20in%20the%20water%20from%20the%20new%20well%20are%20within%20permissible%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Devtarai%20red%20flag%20samples%20from%20all%20six%20districts%20were%20sent%20to%20the%20Bhilai%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20in%20Durg%20and%20the%20readings%20-%20between%2086%20and%20105%20micrograms%20of%20uranium%20per%20litre%20-%20were%20confirmed%20by%20Dr%20Santosh%20Kumar%20Saar%2C%20the%20Chair%20of%20the%20university's%20Chemistry%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBIT%20scientists%20took%20samples%20from%20six%20square%20kilometre%20range%20in%20each%20of%20the%20six%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUranium%20In%20Groundwater%20In%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUranium%20in%20groundwater%20is%20a%20long-standing%20point%20of%20concern%20for%20health%20officials%3B%20in%20January%20last%20year%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Central%20Groundwater%20Board%20said%20it%20had%20crossed%20permissible%20limits%20in%2012%20states%2C%20including%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%3B%20the%20two%20states%20produce%20over%20half%20of%20the%20country's%20wheat%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamples%20from%2013%20other%20states%20had%20uranium%20within%20set%20limits%3B%20those%20from%20Kerala%20had%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20nine%20districts%20of%20Bihar%20reported%20similarly%20high%20levels%20of%20uranium%20in%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhigh-volume-of-uranium-in-groundwater-in-bihar-leaves-authorities-worried-3230442%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHigh%20Volume%20Of%20Uranium%20In%20Bihar%20Groundwater%20Worries%20Authorities%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshok%20Kumar%20Ghosh%2C%20the%20then%20Chairman%20of%20the%20State%20Pollution%20Control%20Board%2C%20told%20news%20agency%20PTI%2C%20%26quot%3BUranium%20contamination%20in%20groundwater%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20serious%20concern%2C%20as%20it%20is%20hazardous%20to%20the%20health%20of%20those%20exposed.%20High%20exposure%20may%20cause%20bone%20toxicity%20and%20impaired%20renal%20function%20and%20cancer%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgajendra-singh-shekhawat-asks-karnataka-govt-to-tackle-uranium-contamination-in-drinking-water-2807068%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKarnataka%20had%20also%20reported%20high%20uranium%20levels%20in%20water%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESolution%20To%20Uranium%20Contamination%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20faced%20with%20the%20uranium-in-water%20problem%2C%20may%20also%20have%20a%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20three%20BIT%20scientists%2C%20led%20by%20Poonam%20Deshmukh%2C%20indicates%20uranium%20can%20be%20filtered%20by%20using%20the%20bark%20of%20a%20gooseberry%20(amla)%20tree.%20Ms%20Deshmukh%20published%20her%20findings%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS2352801X21000825%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGroundwater%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20and%20the%20method%20has%20been%20patented%20but%20not%20implemented%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20that%20if%20there%20is%20concentration%20of%20uranium%20in%20water...%20there%20should%20also%20be%20remedial%20techniques.%20We%20developed%20'bio-adjusting'%20technique%20(and)%20we%20got%20the%20best%20result%20with%20amla%20bark.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELarge-scale%20implementation%20of%20such%20filtering%20techniques%20must%20be%20a%20point%20of%20action%2C%20given%20Chhattisgarh%20is%20home%20to%20four%20known%20deposits%20of%20100%20per%20cent%20grade%20uranium%20-%20three%20of%20which%20are%20Rajnandgaon%20district%2C%20where%20contaminated%20water%20was%20found%20-%20according%20to%20the%20Uranium%20Corporation%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENDTV%20is%20now%20available%20on%20WhatsApp%20channels.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatsapp.com%2Fchannel%2F0029Va4lixw7z4kcvZI9JM12%5C%22%3EClick%20on%20the%20link%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20all%20the%20latest%20updates%20from%20NDTV%20on%20your%20chat.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729584900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-04%2Fpi1ri3i4_well-generic-istock_625x300_21_April_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Furanium-in-drinking-water-in-india-chhattisgarh-red-f